Concerning this aspect I can be quoted in saying:

“The contribution to Croatian statehood that was given by the members of the Croatian Party of Rights happened in the second half of the 19th century. This party represented a real Croatian political movement and with its eloquent manifestations it opened the door to the Croatian intellectuals, writers and others among the Croatian intelligentsia and common people to participate publicly in the work of building the Croatian state movement and a state in Croatia.”

From this we can conclude that except for the fight for freedom in the times of Illyrian Movement, the most important war for freedom was the Croatian struggle for statehood and separate self-governing identity.

I consider that the state we have today with the borders we have today is, in all likelihood, the final administrative determination, based on a series of historical references of already known date. We can of course wait for changes that can neither be predicted in advance, nor for good, nor for bad.
